This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it discusses the emergence of language in multi-agent communication protocols. It also involves techniques for end-to-end learning (cs.AI) and the emergence of grounded human-interpretable language (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the invented languages (cs.SD) and how to improve their compositionality (cs.NE).
